Chaetotaxy
: Leg I: femur, 1-1-1-1 d (centrals), 1 P A; patella, 1 P A; tibia, 1-1 P, 2-3-1 V, a small spur, with an apical long and curved spine (
Fig. 21I
); metatarsus, 1 P, 1-1-2 V, presence of a protuberance (nearly two-thirds of the segment from its base), covered with numerous black blunt spinules (
Fig. 21I
); tarsus, 0. Leg II: femur, 1-1-1-1-1-1 d, 1-1 P A; patella, 0; tibia, 1-1 P, 2-1-3 V; metatarsus, 1-1 P, 3-2-2-2 V; tarsus, 0. Leg III: femur, 1-1-1-1-1 d, 1-1-1 P SUP, 1-1-1 R SUP; patella, 1-2 P, 1 R; tibia, 1-1 P, 1-1 D, 1-1 R, 2-2-3 V; metatarsus, 1-1-1 P, 1-1-1-1 D–P, 1-1- 1-1 D–R, 1-1-1 R, 3-3-3 V; tarsus, 0. Leg IV: femur, 1-1-1-1 d, 1-1-1 P SUP, 1-1 R SUP; patella, 1 P, 1 R; tibia, 1-1 P, 1-1-2 R, 2-2-3 V; metatarsus, 1-1-1 P, 1-1-1-1 D–P, 1-1-1-1-1 D–R, 1-1-1-1 R, 1-2-2-1-3 V; tarsus, 0. Palp (
Fig. 21D, E
): femur, 1-1-1-1 d, 1 P A; patella, 0; tibia, 1-2 P, 1 R A, (width/length: 0.88); tarsus, 0.
